<span id="freeTextContainer15214786521535337017"><b>* * * * * 5 <i>Thank Goodness</i> Stars * * * * *</b><br/><br/>I have been struggling through these last few books, but I have been continuing since my <b>Twinie Amy</b> has been dragging me along. I am so thankful she has been, because I absolutely <b>loved</b> this one!<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1406122733ra/10507578.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>All of the BDB books have side stories and this is something that has driven me a little crazy in the past, but I loved the side stories in this one. I felt these side stories were relevant and because they focused on the Brothers I actually cared what was happen</span>
  <span id="freeText15214786521535337017" style="display:none"><b>* * * * * 5 <i>Thank Goodness</i> Stars * * * * *</b><br><br>I have been struggling through these last few books, but I have been continuing since my <b>Twinie Amy</b> has been dragging me along. I am so thankful she has been, because I absolutely <b>loved</b> this one!<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1406122733ra/10507578.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>All of the BDB books have side stories and this is something that has driven me a little crazy in the past, but I loved the side stories in this one. I felt these side stories were relevant and because they focused on the Brothers I actually cared what was happening. Even the stories that were not directly related were important. <br><br>Now let’s focus on our main story – Manny and Payne. <br><br>Manny…love, love, love…he was sweet, caring and protective of Payne. Payne, V’s twin sister, was strong, loving, independent and I loved her too! She was selfless with Manny, and was willing to risk everything to keep him safe and happy. <b>One of my favorite BDB couples for sure!</b><br><br>On a side note…only 1 more book until I finally get to the epic story of Qhuinn and Blay!<br></span>
