<div id="review_104259236" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/104259236" />
    <a title="UKSandy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3421918-uksandy"><img alt="UKSandy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1300471322p2/3421918.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/104259236?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="UKSandy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="UKSandy" href="/user/show/3421918-uksandy">UKSandy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3421918-uksandy?shelf=march-2011">march-2011</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer104259236&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer104259236" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1539475037114055647">Was this book worth the wait? HELL YEAH IT WAS!<br/><br/>I always knew I was going to like the next BDB book, goes without saying really and I wasn&apos;t really looking forward to Payne&apos;s book as much as the others but oh deary me how wrong was I! I wasn&apos;t really that fussed about Manny either but I JUST LOVE HIM, he is soooooo much more than I expected. He is loving, caring, considerate,HOT and that man has some talents of his own going on!<br/><br/>I loved the fact there were no lessers - What a result!!! I normally </span>
  <span id="freeText1539475037114055647" style="display:none">Was this book worth the wait? HELL YEAH IT WAS!<br /><br />I always knew I was going to like the next BDB book, goes without saying really and I wasn't really looking forward to Payne's book as much as the others but oh deary me how wrong was I! I wasn't really that fussed about Manny either but I JUST LOVE HIM, he is soooooo much more than I expected. He is loving, caring, considerate,HOT and that man has some talents of his own going on!<br /><br />I loved the fact there were no lessers - What a result!!! I normally skim the lesser bits but didn't have to this time although I was hoping to see Lash get pummelled by JM but maybe that is for another book. The band of bastards are very interesting, however, that they are still talking old worlde english when the brothers don't??? and really, they still live in a Castle and eat of pewter plates??<br /><br />Now then Payne, I just loved her, I loved her whole innocence with Manny, her enthsiasim for her new life and most of all the girl kicks ass! Her moments with V were extremely touching. Manny &amp; Payne are just great together, I'm glad the paralysis didn't last but even if it did Manny wouldn't have cared and that is why I love him.<br /><br />V oh lordy V! his sex scenes with Jane were A.M.A.Z.I.N.G!!! There were also some scenes that just pulled at those old heart strings of mine. The scene with Butch well I really felt for Butch and what a friend he is! I don't want to read of anything sexual between V &amp; Butch really, I just love them as brothers. At the end of this book I felt V is now nearly complete much more than he has been in previous books and love the fact he has now "made love" to Jane. I was really shocked to find out that they weren't mated and V didn't have her name on his back, I don't know why I didn't know this earlier! I'm really hoping we get to hear all about their mating scene in the next book as I will feel totally cheated if we don't!<br /><br />Qhuinn *sigh* Qhuinn, what to do with him, I loved the conversation with him and Layla, Qhuinn just needs someone but I also felt extremely sorry for Layla, I know people don't like her but I DO and I hope she gets the HEA I think she deserves. I also hope she is there for Qhuinn when he needs someone to talk to - that is TALK nothing else!<br /><br />Saxton - well still don't like the guy, still don't like that he is still with Blay, just doesn't work for me at all! I'm hoping Qhuinn plucks up the courage and reaches out for *his* man! Now that he has started talking to Layla I'm hoping this is the first step on that yellow brick road for Qhuinn to the lover that is his soul mate.<br /><br />The relationship between Manny &amp; Butch was just FANTASTIC, absolutely bloody brilliant, the two had me in stitches when trying to use the computer and the way Manny knocked V out of the way to get to Payne *sigh* I LOVE HIM!<br /><br />Zsadist you will always have my heart however Manny, you are bloody close, just keep in my line of sight because I got you in mine!<br /><br />I'm looking forward to finding about more about Throe, he really interested me and I want to find out what happened to his sister.<br /><br />So, again was this book worth the wait - OMFG YES, YES, YES!!!<br /><br />JRW you are soooooooooo amazing, for me you just nail it every time and you exceeded my expectations.<br /><br />This book comes 2nd after my beloved Zsadist *heart you Zsadist*</span>
  <a data-text-id="1539475037114055647" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

